[SIZE=5][B]ItemMagnet is back — rebuilt for Paper 1.21+[/B][/SIZE]

[CENTER][I]v1.2.1 · First release since 2021 · Modern survival SMP magnet plugin[/I][/CENTER]

[HR]

[B]It has been a while.[/B]

ItemMagnet went quiet after 2021. If you used the original plugin on older versions, thank you for your patience — this is a full revival built for [B]modern Paper servers[/B], not a quick port.

The core idea is the same: [B]tiered magnet tools[/B] that pull dropped loot toward you. Everything else has been rebuilt for how survival SMPs run today.

[HR]

[SIZE=4][B]What is new in the 1.2.x line[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Paper 1.21.1+[/B] and [B]Java 21+[/B] (tested through Paper 26.1)
[*][B]Visible pull physics[/B] — line-of-sight movement; items slide around corners instead of teleporting through walls
[*][B]Redstone fuel system[/B] — dust recharge, redstone block power surges, live charge/radius on item lore
[*][B]Claim-aware[/B] — Lands, WorldGuard, Towny, and GriefPrevention hooks
[*][B]Three tiers[/B] — Fragment, Survey, Anchor (configurable materials, recipes, unlock gates)
[*][B]Hold modes[/B] — main hand, hotbar, or anywhere in inventory
[*][B]In-game config GUI[/B] — [CODE]/itemmagnet config[/CODE] with tier editor and hot reload
[*][B]XP orb pulling[/B], PlaceholderAPI placeholders, and a public developer API
[/LIST]

[HR]

[SIZE=4][B]Requirements (important)[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Paper 1.21.1 or newer[/B] — required (not vanilla Spigot/CraftBukkit)
[*][B]Java 21+[/B]
[*][B]Folia[/B] — not supported
[/LIST]

Paper is a drop-in replacement on most hosts. If you ran the 2021 build on Spigot, you will need Paper for fuel transfer and modern interact handling.

[HR]

